pullRequest.body:
This PR shows that `C ⥤ D` is enriched over `C ⥤ Type max v' v u` where `C : Type u` with `[Category.{v} C]` and `[Category.{v'} D]`.  To do this, a hom-object is constructed for functors `F G : C ⥤ D`. Applies in particular to simplicial objects being enriched over simplicial sets.

The naming convention says that this should be `homObjEquiv`. Also, I think it would be more common to put `HomObj F G A` on the left of the equivalence.
Can you say why you chose to use an abbrev as opposed to a def with `@[simps!]`?
Use `homObjFunctor` to follow the naming conventions.
Here as well I would put `A -> F.functorHom G` on the LHS.
... and finally, to say consistent, `... -> F.functorHom G` could go on the left.

This lemma (and some of the other lemmas below) should probably go to the other file in this PR, as they're part of the API for the definitions introduced there.

... Actually, looking at the rest of the file, it seems like you may as well just put everything for this PR in one file!

```suggestion
    (x : (((K.functorHom L) ⊗ (L.functorHom M)) ⊗ (M.functorHom N)).obj X) :
```
Otherwise, it looks good to me.
